javadoc:
A _F_ile _S_ystem _R_esource _L_ocator, (name and string format patterned after URLs)

Used to locate a resource (by name) on a "filesystem", in a recursively nested fashion.

The string format of FSRLs is {@code fstype} + "://" + {@code path} + {@code optional_MD5} [ + "|" pipe + {@code FSRL} ]*

See {@link #fromPartString(FSRL, String)} for more format info.

Read the string format from right-to-left for easiest understanding... ie. "file://z|y://x" reads as "file x inside a filesystem y inside a container file z".

FSRL instances are immutable and thread-safe.

Examples (pipes shown in red since they are hard to see):

  • file://dir/subdir -- simplest example, locates a file on local computer filesystem.
  • file://dir/subdir/example.zip|zip://readme.txt -- points to a file named "readme.txt" in a zip file.
  • file://dir/subdir/example.zip|zip://dir/nested.tar|tar://file.txt -- points to a file inside a TAR archive, which is inside a ZIP archive, which is on the local filesystem.
  • file://dir/subdir/example.zip?MD5=1234567|zip://readme.txt?MD5=987654 -- points to a file named "readme.txt" (with a MD5 hash) in a zip file (that has another MD5 hash).

See {@link FSRLRoot} for examples of how FSRL and FSRLRoot's are related.

FSRL's can be created either piecemeal, from the bottom up, starting with a root filesystem FSRL and calling {@link #appendPath(String)} or {@link FSRLRoot#nestedFS(FSRL, String)} methods to create deeper and deeper nested FSRLs,

or

FSRL's can be created from strings using {@link #fromString(String)}.

FSRLs that have a MD5 value are {@link FileSystemService#getFullyQualifiedFSRL(FSRL, ghidra.util.task.TaskMonitor) "fully qualified"}.

methods.name: fromString
methods.comment:
Creates a FSRL from a raw string.  The parent portions of the FSRL
 are not intern()'d so will not be shared with other FSRL instances.
 
 See #fromPartString(FSRL, String) for details of character encoding fixups.

throws.comment: if empty string or bad format

return.comment: new FSRL instance, never null

methods.name: fromString
methods.comment:
Creates a FSRL from a raw string.
 
 See #fromPartString(FSRL, String) for details of character encoding fixups.

throws.comment: if empty string or bad format

return.comment: new FSRL instance, never null

methods.name: fromPartString
methods.comment:
Creates a single FSRL from a FSRL-part string.
 
 A FSRL-part string is defined as protocol_string + "://" + path_string + "?" + param_string.
 
 There should be  no '|' separator characters present in the FSRL-part string.
 
 Backslash characters in the path are normalized to forward slashes after decoding any
 hex encoded character values (ie. %20 becomes ' ' (32) ).  See FSUtilities#escapeEncode(String).

params.name: containerFile
params.comment: the parent container file that contains this filesystem's data

params.name: partStr
params.comment: the string that defines this portion of the FSRL

throws.comment: if the partStr is formatted incorrectly

return.comment: new FSRL instance, who's FSLRRoot is parented on containerFile.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Protected constructor called by static factory methods such as #fromString(String)
 or methods that return a new instance such as #withPath(String).

params.name: parent
params.comment: FSRL parent, null if this instance is root FSRLRoot

params.name: path
params.comment: String path, meaning dependent on context

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment:
Protected constructor called by static factory methods such as #fromString(String)
 or methods that return a new instance such as #withPath(String).

params.name: parent
params.comment: FSRL parent, null if this instance is root FSRLRoot

params.name: path
params.comment: String path, meaning dependent on context

params.name: md5
params.comment: hex string with the md5 hash of the file this FSRL points to, null ok.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the {@link FSRLRoot} object that represents the entire {@link GFileSystem filesystem} for this FSRL.

Never returns NULL, and calling getFS() on a {@link FSRLRoot} object returns itself. @return {@link FSRLRoot} instance that is the parent of this {@link FSRL}, never null.
methods.name: getFS
methods.comment:
Returns the FSRLRoot object that represents the entire
 GFileSystem for this FSRL.
 
 Never returns NULL, and calling getFS() on a FSRLRoot object
 returns itself.

return.comment:
FSRLRoot instance that is the parent of this FSRL, never
 null.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the number of {@link FSRLRoot}s there are in this {@link FSRL}.

A single level FSRL such as "file://path" will return 1.
A two level FSRL such as "file://path|subfs://path2" will return 2.
etc.
@return number of levels in this FSRL, min value returned is 1.
methods.name: getNestingDepth
methods.comment:
Returns the number of FSRLRoots there are in this FSRL.
 
 A single level FSRL such as "file://path" will return 1.
 A two level FSRL such as "file://path|subfs://path2" will return 2.
 etc.

return.comment: number of levels in this FSRL, min value returned is 1.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the full path/filename of this FSRL. Does not include parent filesystem path or info.

"file://path|subfs://subpath/blah" returns "/subpath/blah"

May return null if this instance is a {@link FSRLRoot}. @return string path and filename of this object. Null if this {@link FSRL} is a {@link FSRLRoot}.
methods.name: getPath
methods.comment:
Returns the full path/filename of this FSRL.  Does not include parent filesystem path
 or info.
 
 "file://path|subfs://subpath/blah" returns "/subpath/blah"
 
 May return null if this instance is a FSRLRoot.

return.comment:
string path and filename of this object.  Null if this FSRL is a
 FSRLRoot.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the name portion of this FSRL's path, everything after the last '/'

"file://path/name.ext" returns "name.ext" @return name portion of this FSRL path, or null if path is null also.
methods.name: getName
methods.comment:
Returns the name portion of this FSRL's path, everything after the last '/'
 
 "file://path/name.ext" returns "name.ext"

return.comment: name portion of this FSRL path, or null if path is null also.

methods.name: getName
methods.comment:
Returns the name portion of the FSRL part at parent depth , where 0
 is ourself (equiv to just calling #getName(), 1 is the parent
 container's name, etc.

params.name: nestedDepth
params.comment: relative parent index of FSRL part to query, 0 == this instance.

throws.comment: if nestedDepth is larger than number of FSRL parent parts.

return.comment: name portion of the path of the specified FSRL part.

methods.javadoc:
Returns the MD5 string associated with this file.

NULL if no MD5 value present.

@return md5 string associated with this file object, or null if not present.
methods.name: getMD5
methods.comment:
Returns the MD5 string associated with this file.
 
 NULL if no MD5 value present.

return.comment: md5 string associated with this file object, or null if not present.

methods.name: withMD5
methods.comment:
Creates a new FSRL instance, using the same information as this instance,
 but with a new #getMD5() value.

return.comment: new FSRL instance with the same path and the specified md5 value.

methods.javadoc:
Creates a new {@link FSRL} instance, using the same {@link FSRLRoot} as this instance, but with a new path.

See also {@link #appendPath(String)}.

@param newpath string path @return new {@link FSRL} instance with the specified path.
methods.name: withPath
methods.comment:
Creates a new FSRL instance, using the same FSRLRoot as this instance,
 but with a new path.
 
 See also #appendPath(String).

return.comment: new FSRL instance with the specified path.

methods.name: withPath
methods.comment:
Creates a new FSRL instance using the same path and other metadata
 present in the  instance.
 
 Used when re-root'ing a FSRL path onto another parent object (usually during intern()'ing)

return.comment: new FSRL instance

methods.name: appendPath
methods.comment:
Creates a new FSRL instance, using the same FSRLRoot as this instance,
 combining the current #getPath() with the  value.

return.comment: new FSRL instance with additional path appended.

methods.name: makeNested
methods.comment:
Creates a new FSRLRoot instance that is a child of this FSRL.
 
 See FSRLRoot#nestedFS(FSRL, FSRLRoot) and FSRLRoot#nestedFS(FSRL, String).

return.comment: new FSRLRoot instance

methods.javadoc:
Returns a string containing the full FSRL.

Example: "file://path|subfs://blah?MD5=1234567" @return string with full FSRL
methods.name: toString
methods.comment:
Returns a string containing the full FSRL.
 
 Example: "file://path|subfs://blah?MD5=1234567"

return.comment: string with full FSRL

methods.javadoc:
Returns a string containing the full FSRL, excluding MD5 portions.
@return string with full FSRL, excluding MD5 portions.
methods.name: toPrettyString
methods.comment: Returns a string containing the full FSRL, excluding MD5 portions.

return.comment: string with full FSRL, excluding MD5 portions.

methods.javadoc:
Returns a string containing the full FSRL, without FS "fstype://" portions

Example:

{@code "fsrl://path/filename?MD5=1234|subfsrl://subpath/subfile"}

will result in

{@code "path/filename|subpath/subfile"}. @return formatted string such as: "path/filename|subpath/subfile"
methods.name: toPrettyFullpathString
methods.comment:
Returns a string containing the full FSRL, without FS "fstype://" portions
 
 Example:
 
 
 
 will result in
 
 .

return.comment: formatted string such as: "path/filename|subpath/subfile"

methods.javadoc:
Returns a string containing just the current {@link FSRL} protocol and path.

Example: "file://path|subfs://blah?MD5=123456" returns "subfs://blah?MD5=123456" @return string containing just the current {@link FSRL} protocol and path.
methods.name: toStringPart
methods.comment:
Returns a string containing just the current FSRL protocol and path.
 
 Example: "file://path|subfs://blah?MD5=123456" returns "subfs://blah?MD5=123456"

return.comment: string containing just the current FSRL protocol and path.

methods.javadoc:
Splits a {@link FSRL} into a {@link List}, with each element pointing to each level of the full FSRL.

Example: "file://path|subfs://blah|subfs2://blah2"

Produces a list of 3 elements:
"file://path"
"file://path|subfs://blah"
"file://path|subfs://blah|subfs2://blah2"

@return {@link List} of {@link FSRL} elements pointing to each level of this FSRL.
methods.name: split
methods.comment:
Splits a FSRL into a List, with each element pointing to
 each level of the full FSRL.
 
 Example: "file://path|subfs://blah|subfs2://blah2"
 
 Produces a list of 3 elements:
 "file://path"
 "file://path|subfs://blah"
 "file://path|subfs://blah|subfs2://blah2"

return.comment: List of FSRL elements pointing to each level of this FSRL.

methods.name: isEquivalent
methods.comment: Returns true if the two FSRLs are the same, excluding any MD5 values.

return.comment:
boolean true if this instance is the same as the specified string-ified fsrl,
 ignoring any md5 values.

methods.name: isEquivalent
methods.comment: Returns true if the two FSRLs are the same, excluding any MD5 values.

return.comment:
boolean true if this instance is the same as the specified FSRL, ignoring
 any md5 values.

methods.name: isDescendantOf
methods.comment:
Returns  if this object is a child or descendant of the
 specified  parameter.

return.comment:
boolean true if the specified FSRL is a parent (ignoring md5 hashes)
 of this instance.
